The paper deals with improving the user experience for web search queries related to named entities by augmenting search results with trivia facts. This involves the use of algorithms to mine trivia facts from Wikipedia, which is a task that falls under the purview of information retrieval (cs.IR), natural language processing (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), deep learning (cs.DL), and databases (cs.DB). While the paper does not explicitly mention any of these sub-categories, they are all relevant to the research presented.
